'''Kureo Yuge''' (弓削 是雄) was a {{ill|noble|ja|貴族|12=draft}} and {{ill|onmyōji|ja|陰陽師|12=draft}} of the {{ill|Early Heian period|ja|平安時代|12=draft}}. He held the title {{ill|Junior Fifth Rank|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|12=draft}} and served as Chief of the {{ill|Yin-Yang Bureau|ja|陰陽寮|en:draft|Yin-Yang Bureau|lt=Yin-Yang Bureau|12=draft}}. He was the son of {{ill|Yuge Yasuto|ja|弓削安人|12=draft}}.

== Career ==
Kureo began his service in the Bureau of Onmyō (陰陽寮) during the reign of {{ill|Emperor Seiwa|ja|Emperor Seiwa|12=draft}}, working as an onmyōji. In {{ill|Jōgan|ja|貞観|12=draft}} 6 ({{ill|864|ja|864th year|12=draft}}), he and his father moved their {{ill|honke|ja|本貫|12=draft}} from {{ill|Harima Province|ja|播磨国|12=draft}} to {{ill|Kawachi Province|ja|河内国|12=draft}}.<ref>At the time, Kureo held the rank of {{ill|Junior Eighth Rank|ja|従八位下|1=Junior Eighth Rank|lt=Junior Eighth Rank, Lower Grade|12=draft}}.</ref>

During Emperor Seiwa’s later reign, he continued in various roles within the Bureau of Onmyō. By {{ill|Jōgan|ja|貞観|12=draft}} 15 ({{ill|873|ja|873rd year|12=draft}}), he relocated his honke again to {{ill|Ukyo Sanjō Second Ward|ja|右京三条二坊|12=draft}}. In {{ill|Jōgan|ja|貞観|12=draft}} 19 ({{ill|877|ja|877th year|12=draft}}), upon {{ill|Emperor Yōzei|ja|陽成天皇|12=draft}}'s accession, he was promoted to {{ill|Junior Fifth Rank|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|12=draft}}, and his clan's name was changed from "Ren" (連) to "Sukune" (宿禰).<ref>『日本三代実録』Jōgan 19 (877), April 1 entry.</ref>

In {{ill|Ninna|ja|仁和|12=draft}} 1 ({{ill|885|ja|885th year|12=draft}}), he became Chief of the {{ill|Yin-Yang Bureau|ja|陰陽寮|en:draft|Yin-Yang Bureau|lt=Yin-Yang Bureau|12=draft}}. A record suggests he passed away in {{ill|Engi|ja|延喜|12=draft}} 8 ({{ill|908|ja|908th year|12=draft}}) at the age of 61.

== Folklore ==
Kureo was reputed for his divination skills. A story in the {{ill|Konjaku Monogatari|ja|今昔物語集|12=draft}} recounts his dream interpretation that saved a man's life.<ref>『今昔物語集』巻24第14話 "天文博士弓削是男占夢語".</ref>

In this tale, Kureo warns his fellow traveler, Ban no Tsugutsugu, against returning home due to a prophetic dream. Kureo instructs Tsugutsugu on how to confront the danger. Following the advice, Tsugutsugu discovers an assassin hidden in his house and averts his fate, confirming Kureo’s prophetic prowess.

== Official Positions ==
All details are from the {{ill|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|ja|日本三代実録|12=draft}} unless noted otherwise:
