'''Kureo Yuge''' (弓削 是雄) was a {{ill|noble|ja|貴族|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|onmyōji|ja|陰陽師|qq=draft|qq=draft}} of the {{ill|Early Heian period|ja|平安時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. He held the title {{ill|Junior Fifth Rank|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and served as Chief of the {{ill|Yin-Yang Bureau|ja|陰陽寮|1=Yin-Yang Bureau|2=ja|3=陰陽寮|4=fr|5=Bureau d'Onmyō|6=zh|7=阴阳寮|8=ko|9=음양료|en:draft|Yin-Yang Bureau|lt=Yin-Yang Bureau|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. He was the son of {{ill|Yuge Yasuto|ja|弓削安人|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

== Career ==
Kureo began his service in the Bureau of Onmyō (陰陽寮) during the reign of {{ill|Emperor Seiwa|ja|Emperor Seiwa|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, working as an onmyōji. In {{ill|Jōgan|ja|貞観|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 6 ({{ill|864|ja|864th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), he and his father moved their {{ill|honke|ja|本貫|qq=draft|qq=draft}} from {{ill|Harima Province|ja|播磨国|qq=draft|qq=draft}} to {{ill|Kawachi Province|ja|河内国|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.<ref>At the time, Kureo held the Rank of {{ill|Junior Eighth Rank|ja|従八位下|1=Junior Eighth Rank|lt=Junior Eighth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.</ref>

During Emperor Seiwa’s later reign, he continued in various roles within the Bureau of Onmyō. By {{ill|Jōgan|ja|貞観|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 15 ({{ill|873|ja|873rd year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), he relocated his honke again to {{ill|Ukyo Sanjō Second Ward|ja|右京三条二坊|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. In {{ill|Jōgan|ja|貞観|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 19 ({{ill|877|ja|877th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), upon {{ill|Emperor Yōzei|ja|陽成天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft}}'s accession, he was promoted to {{ill|Junior Fifth Rank|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and his clan's name was changed from "Ren" (連) to "Sukune" (宿禰).<ref>『日本三代実録』Jōgan 19 (877), April 1 entry.</ref>

In {{ill|Ninna|ja|仁和|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 1 ({{ill|885|ja|885th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), he became Chief of the {{ill|Yin-Yang Bureau|ja|陰陽寮|1=Yin-Yang Bureau|2=ja|3=陰陽寮|4=fr|5=Bureau d'Onmyō|6=zh|7=阴阳寮|8=ko|9=음양료|en:draft|Yin-Yang Bureau|lt=Yin-Yang Bureau|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. A record suggests he passed away in {{ill|Engi|ja|延喜|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 8 ({{ill|908|ja|908th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) at the age of 61.

== Folklore ==
Kureo was reputed for his divination skills. A story in the {{ill|Konjaku Monogatari|ja|今昔物語集|qq=draft|qq=draft}} recounts his dream interpretation that saved a man's life.<ref>『今昔物語集』巻24第14話 "天文博士弓削是男占夢語".</ref>

In this tale, Kureo warns his fellow traveler, Ban no Tsugutsugu, against returning home due to a prophetic dream. Kureo instructs Tsugutsugu on how to confront the danger. Following the advice, Tsugutsugu discovers an assassin hidden in his house and averts his fate, confirming Kureo’s prophetic prowess.

== Official Positions ==
All details are from the {{ill|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|ja|日本三代実録|qq=draft|qq=draft}} unless noted otherwise:
* Undated: {{ill|Junior Eighth Rank|ja|従八位下|1=Junior Eighth Rank|lt=Junior Eighth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Onmyōji
* Jōgan 6 (864): Honke moved from Harima Province to Kawachi Province
* Undated: {{ill|Senior Seventh Rank|ja|正七位上|1=Senior Seventh Rank|lt=Senior Seventh Rank, Upper Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Onmyō Assistant
* Jōgan 15 (873): Honke moved to Ukyo Sanjō Second Ward
* Undated: {{ill|Senior Sixth Rank|ja|正六位上|1=Senior Sixth Rank|lt=Senior Sixth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Onmyō Subordinate
* Jōgan 19 (877): Promoted to {{ill|Junior Fifth Rank|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Outer). Clan name changed to Sukune
* Undated: Assistant in Bizen Province
* Genkei 6 (882): Promoted to Junior Fifth Rank (Inner)
* Ninna 1 (885): Appointed Chief of the Bureau of Onmyō
* Engi 8 (908): Passed away<ref name="skf" />

== Genealogy ==
* Father: {{ill|Yuge Yasuto|ja|弓削安人|qq=draft|qq=draft}}<ref>『日本三代実録』Jōgan 6 (864), August 8 entry.</ref>
* Mother: Unknown

