== Folklore ==
Kureo was reputed for his divination skills. A story in the {{ill|Konjaku Monogatari|ja|今昔物語集|qq=draft|qq=draft}} recounts his dream interpretation that saved a man's life.<ref>『今昔物語集』巻24第14話 "天文博士弓削是男占夢語".</ref>

In this tale, Kureo warns his fellow traveler, Ban no Tsugutsugu, against returning home due to a prophetic dream. Kureo instructs Tsugutsugu on how to confront the danger. Following the advice, Tsugutsugu discovers an assassin hidden in his house and averts his fate, confirming Kureo’s prophetic prowess.

== Official Positions ==
All details are from the {{ill|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|ja|日本三代実録|qq=draft|qq=draft}} unless noted otherwise:
* Undated: {{ill|Junior Eighth Rank|ja|従八位下|1=Junior Eighth Rank|lt=Junior Eighth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Onmyōji
* Jōgan 6 (864): Honke moved from Harima Province to Kawachi Province
* Undated: {{ill|Senior Seventh Rank|ja|正七位上|1=Senior Seventh Rank|lt=Senior Seventh Rank, Upper Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Onmyō Assistant
* Jōgan 15 (873): Honke moved to Ukyo Sanjō Second Ward
* Undated: {{ill|Senior Sixth Rank|ja|正六位上|1=Senior Sixth Rank|lt=Senior Sixth Rank, Upper Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Onmyō Subordinate
* Jōgan 19 (877): Promoted to {{ill|Junior Fifth Rank|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Outer). Clan name changed to Sukune
* Undated: Assistant in Bizen Province
* Genkei 6 (882): Promoted to Junior Fifth Rank (Inner)
* Ninna 1 (885): Appointed Chief of the Bureau of Onmyō
* Engi 8 (908): Passed away<ref name="skf" />

== Genealogy ==
* Father: {{ill|Yuge Yasuto|ja|弓削安人|qq=draft|qq=draft}}<ref>『日本三代実録』Jōgan 6 (864), August 8 entry.</ref>
* Mother: Unknown

