'''Kureo Yuge''' (弓削 是雄) was a [[:en:Nobility|noble]] and [[:en:Onmyōji|onmyōji]] of the [[:en:Heian period|Early Heian period]]. He held the title {{ill|Junior Fifth Rank|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|qq=}} and served as Chief of the {{ill|Yin-Yang Bureau|ja|陰陽寮|1=Yin-Yang Bureau|2=ja|3=陰陽寮|4=fr|5=Bureau d'Onmyō|6=zh|7=阴阳寮|8=ko|9=음양료|en:draft|Yin-Yang Bureau|lt=Yin-Yang Bureau|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang Bureau|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang Bureau|qq=}}. He was the son of {{ill|Yuge Yasuto|ja|弓削安人|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yuge Yasuto|qq=}}.

== Career ==
Kureo began his service in the Bureau of Onmyō (陰陽寮) during the reign of {{ill|Emperor Seiwa|ja|Emperor Seiwa|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Seiwa|qq=}}, working as an onmyōji. In [[:en:Zhenguan|Jōgan]] 6 ([[:en:864|864]]), he and his father moved their [[:en:Korean clans|honke]] from [[:en:Harima Province|Harima Province]] to [[:en:Kawachi Province|Kawachi Province]].<ref>At the time, Kureo held the Rank of {{ill|Junior Eighth Rank|ja|従八位下|1=Junior Eighth Rank|lt=Junior Eighth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Eighth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Eighth Rank|qq=}}.</ref>

During Emperor Seiwa’s later reign, he continued in various roles within the Bureau of Onmyō. By [[:en:Zhenguan|Jōgan]] 15 ([[:en:873|873]]), he relocated his honke again to {{ill|Ukyo Sanjō Second Ward|ja|右京三条二坊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ukyo Sanjō Second Ward|qq=}}. In [[:en:Zhenguan|Jōgan]] 19 ([[:en:877|877]]), upon [[:en:Emperor Yōzei|Emperor Yōzei]]'s accession, he was promoted to {{ill|Junior Fifth Rank|ja|従五位下|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fifth Rank|qq=}}, and his clan's name was changed from "Ren" (連) to "Sukune" (宿禰).<ref>『日本三代実録』Jōgan 19 (877), April 1 entry.</ref>

In [[:en:Ninna|Ninna]] 1 ([[:en:885|885]]), he became Chief of the {{ill|Yin-Yang Bureau|ja|陰陽寮|1=Yin-Yang Bureau|2=ja|3=陰陽寮|4=fr|5=Bureau d'Onmyō|6=zh|7=阴阳寮|8=ko|9=음양료|en:draft|Yin-Yang Bureau|lt=Yin-Yang Bureau|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang Bureau|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang Bureau|qq=}}. A record suggests he passed away in [[:en:Engi (era)|Engi]] 8 ([[:en:908|908]]) at the age of 61.

== Folklore ==
Kureo was reputed for his divination skills. A story in the [[:en:Konjaku Monogatarishū|Konjaku Monogatari]] recounts his dream interpretation that saved a man's life.<ref>『今昔物語集』巻24第14話 "天文博士弓削是男占夢語".</ref>

In this tale, Kureo warns his fellow traveler, Ban no Tsugutsugu, against returning home due to a prophetic dream. Kureo instructs Tsugutsugu on how to confront the danger. Following the advice, Tsugutsugu discovers an assassin hidden in his house and averts his fate, confirming Kureo’s prophetic prowess.

